(fifthQuint)Cardiovascular Evaluation of Adult PHA 1 Patients.

 The study includes adult patients with mineralocorticoid receptor mutation as compared with not affected relatives.

 It includes also relatives of adult relative of patients with PHA1 in whom no mutation was found.

 Cardiovascular evaluation is conducted with cardiac and vascular ultrasound assessment and cardiac NMR, ambulatory blood pressure measurement.

 Protocol duration is 2 days .

 Detailed genetic study is conducted in family without identified mutation in MINERALORECEPTOR.

